examples.en: We go to church regularly.
I see them pretty regularly.
We meet regularly, once a month.
She attends class regularly.
She visits her doctor regularly.
Do your bowels move regularly?
She regularly goes for a run before breakfast.
The water gets tested regularly.
The sales team meets regularly.
Nightmares assailed him regularly.
It's important to exercise regularly.
Check and adjust the brakes regularly.
Strong winds regularly sweep the islands.
I patronize the library regularly.
I regularly called in at his office for news.
She has been exercising regularly to develop her back muscles.
The plants are regularly spaced.
Wash your cat's bedding regularly.
He eats right and exercises regularly.
Letters arrived regularly from his children.
The media regularly violates people's privacy.
Many Christians regularly confess to a priest.
As it grows, a snake will regularly shed its skin.
College students regularly getting hammered at keggers.
I became rather flabby after I stopped exercising regularly.
University teachers must publish regularly to gain promotion.
To the man sleeping regularly in doorways homelessness is real.
More than half the students in this school are shooting up regularly.
The plant should be misted regularly.
She goes out to dinner quite regularly.
